947	https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/2025-reuse-summit-tickets-1530087756669?aff=ebdssbdestsearch	event-bright	Title: 2025 Reuse Summit\\nShort Description: Risk and Resilience: Building a Reuse-Ready Future\\nLocation: The Institution of Structural Engineers 47-58 Bastwick Street London EC1V 3PS United Kingdom\\nCost: 30  90\\nDates: Thu, 16 Oct 2025 13:00 - 17:30 BST\\nDescription: In the next 10 minutes globally:We will extract 50,000 tonnes of iron ore.5 million bricks will be produced.The construction, demolition, and excavation industry will generate 38,000 tonnes of waste.And each year, the global construction sector emits around 10 gigatonnes of CO  the equivalent of 30 million Boeing 747s.The ASBP Reuse Summit 2025 explores how material reuse can help tackle these environmental and systemic challenges, as part of our ongoing Reuse Now campaign. This years summit focuses on the link between reuse, risk mitigation, and resilience, highlighting practical, strategic pathways to reduce embodied carbon, strengthen supply chains and future-proof business.At our third annual summit, attendees will hear from forward-thinking practitioners and thought leaders who are reshaping how we approach design, demolition, and material reuse. The event features interactive panels and expert-led sessions on topics such as:Risk & Resilience - Moving Circular Economy out of the sustainability siloA contractor-led panel exploring reuse and circular economy at a strategic impact level. Discussions will address the risks of inaction, and how contractors are working internally and across their supply chains to build resilience, upskill teams, and embed reuse into core operations. Well explore double materiality and related reporting standards. With evolving compliance timelines and growing expectations around circularity, attendees will gain insight into the implications of upcoming regulations, working closely with supply chains, and how to leverage circular strategies alongside future disclosure requirements.Addressing the Perceived & Actual Risks of Structural ReuseSteel, timber, concrete real vs. perceived risks in reusing structural materials. This session will discuss the latest insights across performance, safety, insurance, and investor confidence, along with real-world examples that show how structural reuse is being delivered in practice. Well explore the decision-making process around choosing the right material, in the right quantities, for the right job.People & Behaviours  how to create the best chance of success for reclamation and reuse?Shifting mindsets - from toolbox talks and exemplar site visits to the importance of clear brief - this session dives into the behavioural and cultural enablers of successful reuse. We'll highlight the importance of early engagement, cross-disciplinary collaboration, timely intervention and education. What mistakes are made? What has worked so far? What more is needed? And how can support be scaled to accelerate change?Key detailsDate: Thursday 16th OctoberTimings: 13:00-17:30 followed by drinks and networking until 19:30Location: The Institution of Structural EngineersInternational HQ, 47-58 Bastwick Street, London, EC1V 3PSCosts:  25+VAT for ASBP members,  50+VAT for members of IStructE, IDE, and NFDC,  75 +VAT general admission	2025 Reuse Summit: Risk and Resilience: Building a Reuse-Ready Future	The ASBP Reuse Summit 2025 delves into how material reuse mitigates risks and builds resilience within the construction sector, aligning with their ongoing Reuse Now campaign. This vital event takes place on 16 October 2025.	The ASBP Reuse Summit 2025 delves into how material reuse mitigates risks and builds resilience within the construction sector, aligning with their ongoing Reuse Now campaign.	The construction industry faces immense challenges, from extracting vast quantities of raw materials and generating significant waste to contributing substantially to global CO emissions. The ASBP Reuse Summit 