are opportunity to experience the scale, history, and ongoing transformation of one of Liverpools most iconic dockland sites.	Visit to Stanley Dock, Liverpool: RIBA North West HCS Group	Join us for a guided tour through stunning industrial architecture, hidden heritage stories, and the ongoing restoration thats shaping Stanley Docks future. Step behind the scenes at one of Liverpools most iconic dockland sites on 11 September 2025.	Join us for a guided tour through stunning industrial architecture, hidden heritage stories, and the ongoing restoration thats shaping Stanley Docks future. Step behind the scenes at one of Liverpools most iconic dockland sites.	Discover the impressive ongoing transformation of Stanley Dock, Liverpool, a site often hailed as Europe's largest adaptive re-use project. This exclusive guided tour, led by the RIBA North West Heritage, Conservation, and Sustainability Group alongside John Hinchliffe, offers an unparalleled opportunity to explore monumental listed buildings like Jesse Hartleys warehouses, the vast Tobacco Warehouse, and the historic Hydraulic Pumphouse.\n\nOnce thriving but long derelict, the site is now experiencing an ambitious revival under Harcourt Developments. You'll gain insight into the complex challenges and innovative solutions involved in converting these immense structures, from the acclaimed Titanic Hotel and Rum Warehouse to the first phases of the Tobacco Warehouse. The tour includes exploring building exteriors, stepping inside key renovated spaces, glimpsing the District Heat Centre, and observing the new Stanley Locks social housing. This visit is an invaluable chance to witness large-scale heritage conservation and regeneration firsthand.	11 Sep 2025, 17:3020:30	20250911	Stanley Dock, corner of Regent Street and Saltney Street, Liverpool, UK	5-6	t	16655	draft	2025-08-11 15:17:25.083796	2025-08-11 14:18:15.93082	232
