1600	https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/visual-branding-creative-direction-for-business-owners-tickets-1474122121949?aff=ebdssbdestsearch	event-bright	Title: Visual Branding & Creative Direction for Business Owners\\nShort Description: This workshop is to help teach how to approach & create a visual brand for your business and yourself, and develop your creative direction.\\nLocation: BIPC, Jubilee Library Jubilee Street Brighton BN1 1GE United Kingdom\\nCost: Free\\nDates: Tue, 30 Sep 2025 10:15 - 11:45 BST\\nDescription: About this eventThere is a saying that a picture can create a thousand words, and this couldnt be more true in the business world. To help you and your business stand out from the crowd and set you apart from your competitors, its important you create a strong visual brand and use it frequently to showcase your story, products, and services. This workshop will provide you with insights, tips and techniques on how to create the right visual brand and creative strategy for you.Agenda topics90 min workshop with time for Q&A.The workshop will focus on: Understanding your brand identity: How to define what your business stands for and how it translates your values into visual language. Building a visual identity with purpose: Choosing imagery, style, and tone that reflect your story, not just what's trendy. Creating visual consistency across platforms: How to visually translate your brand from your website to social media, packaging, and even pitch decks. Developing your creative direction over time: Tips on evolving your brand visuals as your business grows, without losing its core identity.About the SpeakerXavier Buendia is an award-winning, internationally published food, portrait, and documentary photographer and creative director.Originally from Mexico City, Xavi has lived in Brighton since 2009 and became renowned as a premier professional photographer in the hospitality industry. This included capturing the exquisite nature of fine dining, working with well-known chefs such as Monica Galetti, Tom Aikens, and Douglas McMaster, to photographing inspiring stories for independent restaurants, cafes, bars, vineyards, and drinks brands across Sussex, like Ridgeview Wine Estate and The Ginger Pig. During the pandemic, Xavi expanded his practice beyond food, earning an MA in documentary photography. His work evolved to explore human potential, capturing physical, intellectual, and emotional depth through portraiture, documentary, architecture, and personal branding photography. His ability to strip away stereotypes and present subjects authentically has attracted diverse clients from Connected Brighton to PEBE and The Launchpad Collective.Xavi mostly works with independent businesses and enjoys the challenge of creating powerful visuals that help small businesses grow. At the heart of Xavis business is a belief in craft, community, and meaningful storytelling that focuses on human potential. Rooted in a sustainable, purpose-led philosophy, his work champions quality over quantity, slow creation over fast trends, and connection over likes and clicks. Xavi aims to inspire others to see the value in independent voices and ideas that last.This is an in-person event at BIPC, 1st floor of Jubilee Library, Brighton.Following the event, the BIPC will send you a feedback form which we would be grateful if you could complete to allow us to monitor the success of our events.- ------------------Increase your chances of business successBusiness & IP Centre Sussex supports people to start, grow and protect their businesses in Sussex. Come and access our free market research and intellectual property databases and take part in our regular programme of workshops, webinars and networking events.W hat if I don't live / have my business in Sussex?Find your local BIPC here to find out how they can help you: https://www.bl.uk/business-and-ip-centre/national-network- ------------------FAQsWhat is your cancellation policy?The majority of our events are free, but places are often limited - especially for in-person events, therefore please make sure you cancel your place, if you are unable to attend. You can cancel through your Eventbrite booking or emailing bipc@brighton-hove.co.uk.Can I attend if I'm not a member of the library?Absolutely! Any Sussex based business/ person with a business idea is welcome. Though we always recommend joining the library as it's free and will make accessing our databases, books and publications much easier.How can I find out about any news & upcoming events?So glad you asked - we have a newsletter!You can also follow us on Twitter, LinkedIn, Facebook and Instagram for the latest goings-on.	Visual Branding & Creative Direction for Business Owners	This workshop will teach you how to approach and create a compelling visual brand for your business and yourself, along with developing your creative direction. Occurring on 30 September 2025.	This workshop will teach you how to approach and create a compelling visual brand for your business and yourself, along with developing your creative direction.	Discover the power of a compelling visual brand in this insightful workshop, designed to help business owners, including architectural practice leaders, distinguish themselves in a competitive market. Led by award-winning photographer and creative director Xavier Buendia, this 90-minute session will equip you with essential strategies to define and express your business's unique identity. You'll explore how to translate your core values into a distinctive visual language, selecting imagery, style, and tone that authentically narrate your story. Learn to establish seamless visual consistency across all platforms, from your website and social media to professional presentations, ensuring your brand resonates powerfully with your target audience. The workshop also provides valuable tips on evolving your creative direction as your business grows, maintaining a strong, cohesive identity.