ty for the audience to ask questions via chat messages or voice.Accessibility:We strive to ensure our events are accessible. If you have any questions on how to join or participate in this event, please emailriba.sse@riba.orgbefore the event date and time.The joining link to the talk will be sent out a week before the event.	RIBA South Conservation online talk: Flint work with Duncan Berry	Explore the enduring legacy and modern revival of flintwork with master craftsman Duncan Berry in this online talk. Join the discussion on 15 October 2025.	Explore the enduring legacy and modern revival of flintwork with master craftsman Duncan Berry in this online talk.	Discover the fascinating world of flintwork in this insightful online talk with renowned craftsman Duncan Berry. This session, hosted by the RIBA South Conservation Group, will delve into the rich history and diverse applications of flint, a material that has graced our built environment for centuries, from Roman constructions to contemporary high-status architectural projects. Participants will gain a comprehensive understanding of different flint types, a range of finishes, and the intricate techniques required to transform a simple stock wall into a work of art. The discussion will also cover modern construction methods, the crucial role of mortars, and the importance of collaborating with skilled contractors to ensure exceptional quality results. Whether you're working in an area rich with flint landscapes or simply curious about this unique material, this talk offers invaluable technical insights and a deeper appreciation for its lasting relevance in architecture. Architects will find this session particularly useful for enhancing their knowledge of traditional materials, conservation practices, and integrating heritage crafts into modern design.	15 Oct 2025, 13:0014:00	20251015	Online	Free	t	17609	draft	2025-08-25 17:28:53.579053	2025-08-25 17:09:16.9937	321
1488	https://nla.london/events/history-of-the-east-india-company-on-the-thames	nla	Title: History of the East India Company on the Thames\\nEvent Type: Talk\\nDate-Time: Friday 03 October 2025 12:30 - 13:00\\nEvent Details: Free Book now Venue The London Centre3 AldermanburyLondonEC2V 7HH Accessibility There are two ways of entering the London Centre: either up 3 steps with a handrail on either side, or via a platform lift. There are gender-neutral and accessible toilets on the lower ground floor, which can be accessed via a flight of stairs.If you would like more information about the space, or have any further access requirements, please let us know how we can best accommodate these, by emailing events@nla.london. Share this event\\nDescription: Join us for a model talk exploring the history of the East India Company on the Thames. The story of the company is a story of water. Britain and other European nations expanded their rule across different parts of the world due to their Naval prowess. Their colonial exploits shaped the world inside and outside their borders. This includes the river Thames - a conduit to the Empire. In this model talk, we will see the sites in London connected to the East India Company and shaped aspects of its moral law, politics, economy, cuisine and built environment. Speaker biographies Manasi Pophale Creative Director, History Speak	History of the East India Company on the Thames: A Model Talk	Explore the profound influence of the East India Company on the River Thames and London's built environment in this insightful model talk. This event takes place on 03 October 2025.	Explore the profound influence of the East India Company on the River Thames and London's built environment in this insightful model talk.	Delve into the fascinating and complex history of the East India Company and its indelible mark on the River Thames and London. This compelling model talk will highlight how the company's formidable naval prowess drove Britain's g