1473	https://www.architecture.com/whats-on/riba-south-conservation-in-person-tour-of-rochester-cathedral	riba	Title: RIBA South Conservation: In person - Tour of Rochester Cathedral\\nEvent Type: Tours\\nShort Description: Join us with speaker John Bailey for our October building tour and discussion exploring the care and conservation of Rochester Cathedral\\nDate: 22 October 2025, 2pm to 6pm\\nPlace: Rochester Cathedral, The Precinct, Rochester, ME1 1SX\\nContact: riba.sse@riba.org\\nCost: From 12.50 (excl. VAT and Fees)\\nDescription: Join us for the third of our 2025 RIBA South Conservation Group in-person events with a special tour of Rochester Cathedral, led by John Bailey, Director at Thomas Ford & Partners.Rochester Cathedralis one of Englands most significant historic buildings, embodying centuries of worship, craftsmanship, and community life. Over the past decade, an extensive programme of conservation work has been carried out, safeguarding its fabric while supporting its ongoing use as a place of worship and heritage.About the SpeakerJohn Bailey is a Director ofThomas Ford & Partners, a practice with nearly a century of experience in historic building conservation. Over the past 35 years, John has worked with around 600 ecclesiastical buildings, including the care of three English cathedrals. His expertise extends to work with the National Trust and many significant historic sites. A former Chairman of the SPAB and President of the EASA, John is also a three-time winner of the King of Prussias Gold Medal.Agenda1:45pm  Meet at the North Door, Rochester Cathedral2pm to 4pm  Guided tour of Rochester Cathedral with John BaileyFrom 4pm  Light refreshments and networking at The George Vaults, RochesterPlaces are limited, book early to avoid disappointment.AccessibilityWe strive to ensure our events are accessible for all. Occasionally, our off-site visits may involve steps and uneven terrain- please contact us atriba.sse@riba.orgto discuss the route for specific tours and events.	RIBA South Conservation: In person Tour of Rochester Cathedral	Explore the intricate care and conservation of Rochester Cathedral during a special in-person tour led by renowned expert John Bailey. This unique event takes place on 22 October 2025.	Explore the intricate care and conservation of Rochester Cathedral during a special in-person tour led by renowned expert John Bailey.	Join the RIBA South Conservation Group for an exclusive in-person tour of Rochester Cathedral, one of England's most historically significant buildings. Led by John Bailey, Director at Thomas Ford & Partners, this event offers a deep dive into the extensive conservation work that has safeguarded the cathedral's fabric over the past decade, ensuring its continued use as a vital place of worship and heritage. Attendees will gain invaluable insights into the complexities of preserving historic structures, from architectural challenges to the delicate balance of maintaining both historical integrity and modern functionality. John Bailey, with nearly four decades of experience and numerous accolades in historic building conservation, will share his profound expertise, covering around 600 ecclesiastical buildings including three English cathedrals. The tour will conclude with light refreshments and a networking opportunity at The George Vaults, providing a chance to connect with peers and discuss the day's learnings. This event is highly beneficial for architects looking to enhance their understanding of heritage conservation, materials science, and the adaptive reuse of historic buildings.	22 Oct 2025, 14:0018:00	20251022	Rochester Cathedral, The Precinct, Rochester, ME1 1SX, UK	From 12.50	t	17646	draft	2025-08-25 17:31:32.843604	2025-08-25 17:09:16.999777	322
